# Enums — a fixed set of constants

## A closed set of values

- Each constant is a **singleton** instance
- `values()` and `valueOf(...)` come for free; great with `switch`

```java
public enum HttpMethod { GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, PATCH; }
```

## Enums are full classes

```java
OK(200, "ok"), NOT_FOUND(404, "not found");
// fields + constructor + methods: NOT_FOUND.code() -> 404
```

- Stronger than the integer-flag enums of older languages
